See the comment to this class."""@en
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001828
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001828> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We suggest to revise definitions of “anthropogenic environment” and “anthopised ecosystem” for consistently clarifying the two. ClimOO Ontology builds its representation on the latter as lowest leaf of the EnvO hierarchy."""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000> rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                      owl:unionOf ( :ClimOO_0000037
                                                                                                    :ClimOO_0000045
                                                                                                  )
                                                                                    ]
                                                               ] ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
For ClimOO Ontology purposes, we restricted this class to processes having as occurrent part only environmental system interactions and interaction among environmental systems and related environments. We aim to strictly focus on systems, avoiding possible alternative generalized interpretations of this class and related subclasses. Processes classifiable under these classes are to be intended in a conventional sense (examples may include system activities and practices), wheatear related interactions are to be intended as more atomic events composing such processes."""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500026
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500026> rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000> ;
                                               <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
A process during which human, pertaining to an environmental system or its environment, apply technology to alter the magnitude, duration, rate, or impact of an environmental process."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment: 
For ClimOO purposes, we revised this class definition and its hierarchy position, focusing its application to environmental systems and related process.
See comments to https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000065 and http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500027"""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500027
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500027> <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans part of that environmental system or its environment."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
It seems that the definition of this class requires revisions to clarify reference to anthropogenic environment systems and anthropized ecosystems as well as to possibly align with related “environmental system process” and “ecosystem process” classes’ definitions."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
Reference to related system interactions can be added as needed. See the comment to the “environmental system process” class.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
We created a class specific for processes pertaining to anthopised ecosystem, considering this class as referring to those generally driven by human action. This is our understanding from the definition and related subclasses. We made some revision to related hierarchies. We revised the definition to specify that we are refering to human part of the system or part of its environmental (this also applies to subclasses).

See https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000065"""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000043
